Package frc.robot.management

Class TrajectoryLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • frc.robot.management.TrajectoryLoader
  • public class TrajectoryLoader
extends java.lang.Object
    A custom class to load trajectories that are put at the root of the deploy directory. To a certain degree, this is somewhat cursed because loops are a bit of a controversial thing to use within frc code. However, for this specific use case of loading many files on robot code start, this should be appropriate.

        public TrajectoryLoader()

      • concatenateTrajectories

        public void concatenateTrajectories​(java.lang.String... trajectoryNames)
        Method for stringing trajectories together back to back into a single parent trajectory. The first trajectory passed into the method becomes the parent trajectory that will be altered DIRECTLY in the dictionary, so use with caution.
        Parameters:
        trajectoryNames - Name of each trajectory to concatinate back to back
